                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/rest/edit/master/knpu/episode2/get-one-battle.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Next, let's keep going with viewing a single battle. Scenario: GETting a
single battle. And thinking about this, we're going to need to make sure
that there's a battle in the database first. I'm going to use similar language
as before to create a Fred programmer and a project called project_facebook.
I also have another step that allows me to say And there has been a battle between
"Fred" and "project_facebook":</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="0e18b039d6">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
