<p>From here, life is really familiar. First, do we need security? - always ask
yourself that. I'm going to decide that anyone can fetch battle details out
without being authenticated. So we won't add any protection.</p>
<p>We <em>will</em> need to go and query for the <code>Battle</code> object that represents the
given id. We always want to check if that matches anything, and if it doesn't,
we want to return a really nice 404 response. In episode 1, we did that by
using a function called <code>throw404</code>. That's going to throw a special exception,
which is mapped to a 404 status code, and because we have our nice error handling,
the <code>ApiProblem</code> response format will be returned:</p>
